03:52.591 --> 04:00.861
whether I would be granted tenure there or not, and 
knew if I was not going to receive tenure, a

03:52.591 --> 04:00.861
decision would be a very easy one. But

04:01.762 --> 04:14.458
if I did receive tenure, I actually served on the 
Cornell faculty as an associate professor for two

04:01.762 --> 04:14.458
months back to Texas A&M. That was probably the 
hardest professional decision I've ever made.

04:19.817 --> 04:25.933
You can look back even to this day and wonder, I 
guess, in some respects, whether it was the right

04:19.817 --> 04:25.933
decision or not. Well, a lot of things played into 
it. We were about 1,800 miles from my family, and we

04:28.960 --> 04:36.888
were 1,000 miles from my wife's family, and they 
were 1,000 miles apart. And that made any kind of,

04:37.990 --> 04:45.878
well, it took all the vacation that we had in the 
summer in those days with young children. We'd

04:47.680 --> 04:51.724
spend three weeks vacation, and we'd spend about 
half of it on the road. And so that was a strong

04:52.825 --> 04:55.228
motivator. motivating factor. I did not know 
whether my wife, who was a native of Wisconsin,

04:56.961 --> 05:02.535
whom I met during my PhD years,

